WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:07.882 --> 00:00:08.800 position:50% align:center
Well?

00:00:08.883 --> 00:00:11.052 position:50% align:center
Yeah. He's forced our hand.

00:00:24.107 --> 00:00:26.317 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:00:30.321 --> 00:00:32.991 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:00:40.832 --> 00:00:45.837 position:50% align:center
[grunts, yells]

00:00:56.848 --> 00:00:58.058 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:58.475 --> 00:00:59.684 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:01:04.481 --> 00:01:05.690 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:10.403 position:50% align:center
That's enough!

00:01:10.487 --> 00:01:13.448 position:50% align:center
Stop! Back off!

00:01:13.531 --> 00:01:16.785 position:50% align:center
[KAREN, FUBUKI grunting]

00:01:16.868 --> 00:01:19.204 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Karen. This has to end.

00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:22.374 position:50% align:center
I didn't realize the depths
of your suffering before.

00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:24.709 position:50% align:center
Save it.

00:01:24.793 --> 00:01:28.129 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] You've done
more than anyone should.

00:01:28.213 --> 00:01:30.965 position:50% align:center
But listen, it's over now.

00:01:31.049 --> 00:01:34.094 position:50% align:center
I don't want you to feel this
pain, and neither would she!

00:01:35.011 --> 00:01:36.262 position:50% align:center
Shut your mouth!

00:01:36.346 --> 00:01:37.806 position:50% align:center
Face it!

00:01:37.889 --> 00:01:41.351 position:50% align:center
You and I have to find a way
to go on living in this world!

00:01:41.434 --> 00:01:43.895 position:50% align:center
Even though Alice
isn't here with us.

00:01:43.978 --> 00:01:45.188 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:49.401 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Trust me, I know how you feel.

00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:50.777 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:55.365 position:50% align:center
But still, she's gone...
for good.

00:01:55.448 --> 00:01:58.076 position:50% align:center
And now... it's just us.

00:02:01.746 --> 00:02:03.540 position:50% align:center
[KAREN gasps]

00:02:03.623 --> 00:02:07.919 position:50% align:center
Please, Karen, we need
you to help us out.

00:02:08.003 --> 00:02:10.505 position:50% align:center
Go to the Chronos
Terminal and correct

00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:13.049 position:50% align:center
all the entanglements
you caused.

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:14.467 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
If you don't,

00:02:14.551 --> 00:02:17.554 position:50% align:center
you'll shut the door
on all our futures.

00:02:17.637 --> 00:02:19.848 position:50% align:center
And we refuse
to let that happen.

00:02:19.931 --> 00:02:21.933 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Put a stop to this now.

00:02:22.017 --> 00:02:25.603 position:50% align:center
For your own sake, and for
everyone else you care about.

00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:34.362 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] I see. It seems
this is as far as I got.

00:02:34.446 --> 00:02:38.992 position:50% align:center
Well, then... Perhaps this
will be a choice, too.

00:02:39.075 --> 00:02:40.660 position:50% align:center
My last one.

00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:47.208 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI sighs]

00:02:47.292 --> 00:02:48.376 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:02:48.460 --> 00:02:49.961 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:51.254 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:02:58.011 --> 00:03:03.016 position:50% align:center
♪

00:04:38.028 --> 00:04:40.739 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR A] Hey! What are
you seeing on your screen?

00:04:40.822 --> 00:04:43.742 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR B] Nothing good.
It's too much data to process!

00:04:43.825 --> 00:04:46.119 position:50% align:center
The growth rate
is insanely high.

00:04:46.202 --> 00:04:47.996 position:50% align:center
If this keeps up...

00:04:48.079 --> 00:04:50.415 position:50% align:center
There are too many
to quantify!

00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.541 position:50% align:center
[OPERATORS gasp]

00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:53.209 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR D]
Dammit, it's not working!

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:55.003 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR E]
No! We got cut off!

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.129 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR B gasps]

00:04:56.212 --> 00:04:57.130 position:50% align:center
What do we do?

00:04:57.213 --> 00:04:58.757 position:50% align:center
I'll shut down the system!

00:05:01.593 --> 00:05:03.011 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:05:05.597 --> 00:05:07.891 position:50% align:center
[OPERATIONS DIRECTOR A]
There's nothing more we can do.

00:05:07.974 --> 00:05:09.851 position:50% align:center
Now we just wait.

00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:17.734 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Hm...

00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:43.343 position:50% align:center
[KAREN gasps]

00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:44.260 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Good morning.

00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:48.515 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Huh...? Fubuki.

00:05:48.598 --> 00:05:51.559 position:50% align:center
Doesn't the commander have
more important business?

00:05:51.643 --> 00:05:55.605 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Hm. Actually, we may
have lucked out for once.

00:05:55.689 --> 00:05:59.067 position:50% align:center
For some reason, the Others
have fallen unusually silent.

00:06:01.945 --> 00:06:03.446 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Perhaps because
they fear the same thing

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:05.073 position:50% align:center
that we humans do.

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:12.080 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] You know,
Alice told me something.

00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:15.083 position:50% align:center
She said, "I wish Karen
smiled more often.

00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:18.420 position:50% align:center
He looks kind of
nice with a smile."

00:06:18.503 --> 00:06:22.298 position:50% align:center
I haven't seen you smile
even once since that day.

00:06:22.382 --> 00:06:25.760 position:50% align:center
Then again, it was a rare sight
to begin with, I suppose.

00:06:28.763 --> 00:06:31.599 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] I doubt I can take
away the pain you feel.

00:06:33.309 --> 00:06:36.813 position:50% align:center
But still, I refuse
to give up hoping.

00:06:36.896 --> 00:06:41.818 position:50% align:center
I want you to move on with
your life, Karen, and one day,

00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:46.781 position:50% align:center
I hope you can find a reason
to smile, here, in this world.

00:06:49.534 --> 00:06:51.953 position:50% align:center
What you're saying is...
you want me to correct

00:06:52.037 --> 00:06:54.539 position:50% align:center
my entanglements and
make the Gate disappear.

00:06:54.622 --> 00:06:55.540 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Hm?

00:06:55.623 --> 00:06:57.083 position:50% align:center
I hear you,

00:06:57.167 --> 00:07:00.128 position:50% align:center
but if we can do that, you must
know what else we could do.

00:07:00.211 --> 00:07:01.546 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI grunts]

00:07:04.716 --> 00:07:07.344 position:50% align:center
--[knocking]
--[door opens]

00:07:07.427 --> 00:07:09.346 position:50% align:center
Oh, Major General.

00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:12.223 position:50% align:center
So you finally came to.

00:07:12.307 --> 00:07:13.892 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Karen...

00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:18.521 position:50% align:center
We're ready to carry
out the operation,

00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.815 position:50% align:center
but we'll need your assistance.

00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:23.109 position:50% align:center
Unless, you're too weak?

00:07:23.193 --> 00:07:25.236 position:50% align:center
Sorry, what?

00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:26.446 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] What have you
been fighting me over

00:07:26.529 --> 00:07:28.948 position:50% align:center
this whole time?

00:07:29.032 --> 00:07:29.991 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
The Kunad Gate.

00:07:30.075 --> 00:07:33.036 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Yes, but it isn't just that.

00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:35.872 position:50% align:center
The Extinction Belt
will be destroyed.

00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:37.832 position:50% align:center
How is that possible?

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:40.377 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Your brother Kaito
drafted a strategy by which

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:43.755 position:50% align:center
the Extinction Belt would be
consumed inside the Kunad Gate.

00:07:43.838 --> 00:07:46.758 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but it wouldn't work.

00:07:46.841 --> 00:07:49.928 position:50% align:center
Even using Kasane's
and my gravikinesis,

00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:51.805 position:50% align:center
we'd need more power...

00:07:51.888 --> 00:07:54.140 position:50% align:center
Unless...!

00:07:54.224 --> 00:07:56.351 position:50% align:center
Our last attempt was a failure

00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.062 position:50% align:center
and that was using all the
brains in New Himuka.

00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:00.313 position:50% align:center
That's why this time,

00:08:00.397 --> 00:08:03.650 position:50% align:center
we'll access Arahabaki
on our own strength.

00:08:03.733 --> 00:08:05.652 position:50% align:center
The city's network
is frozen now,

00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:08.738 position:50% align:center
but the supercomputer
itself is still functioning.

00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:13.576 position:50% align:center
If we use SAS, we should be
able to boost our psionic power.

00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:16.538 position:50% align:center
Arahabaki's run through
every possible simulation

00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:18.248 position:50% align:center
over several hundred years.

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.083 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
I'm still not sure.

00:08:20.166 --> 00:08:22.544 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI] Well, there is one
problem with this plan.

00:08:23.753 --> 00:08:26.715 position:50% align:center
The power output will
be massively amplified.

00:08:26.798 --> 00:08:29.843 position:50% align:center
There's no way to know if you
and Kasane can handle it.

00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:36.808 position:50% align:center
Even if there's just the
smallest chance, we have to try.

00:08:36.891 --> 00:08:38.476 position:50% align:center
It's settled, then.

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:43.023 position:50% align:center
The Gate and the
Belt all at once?

00:08:43.106 --> 00:08:45.191 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a tall order.

00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:48.903 position:50% align:center
If it works, then we'll be
able to save countless lives.

00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:52.449 position:50% align:center
We can't! Yuito's been
pushed to his limit!

00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:55.118 position:50% align:center
If he keeps on fighting
then he could die.

00:08:55.201 --> 00:08:56.828 position:50% align:center
Don't you guys get that?

00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:59.039 position:50% align:center
[LUKA, KASANE, KAGERO sigh]

00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:06.171 position:50% align:center
Hanabi has a good point.
Yuito needs to sit this out.

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:09.382 position:50% align:center
I'm not so sure.
If we used Arahabaki,

00:09:09.466 --> 00:09:12.010 position:50% align:center
then our power would
be off the charts,

00:09:12.093 --> 00:09:14.262 position:50% align:center
but would Karen and Kasane's
strength alone be enough

00:09:14.346 --> 00:09:16.931 position:50% align:center
to move the Extinction Belt?

00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:19.893 position:50% align:center
Honestly. The Belt's so massive,

00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:22.520 position:50% align:center
I'm not sure anything would be.

00:09:22.604 --> 00:09:25.440 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI] Even so, we don't
have any other options.

00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:28.151 position:50% align:center
The time to be
cautious is over now.

00:09:28.234 --> 00:09:30.653 position:50% align:center
We might as well go
all in on this plan.

00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:34.074 position:50% align:center
True, but...

00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:36.701 position:50% align:center
[LUKA gasps]
Yuito.

00:09:36.785 --> 00:09:39.204 position:50% align:center
I'm late, sorry.

00:09:39.287 --> 00:09:41.164 position:50% align:center
There you are, Yuito!

00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:42.916 position:50% align:center
You look terrible.

00:09:42.999 --> 00:09:45.335 position:50% align:center
You really need
to get more rest!

00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:47.462 position:50% align:center
Nah, don't worry about me.

00:09:47.545 --> 00:09:50.840 position:50% align:center
Are you serious?
You can barely stand up!

00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:54.344 position:50% align:center
Hanabi. There's no choice.

00:09:54.427 --> 00:09:56.971 position:50% align:center
You'll all support me
through SAS, right?

00:09:57.055 --> 00:09:58.807 position:50% align:center
It'll be okay.

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.308 position:50% align:center
Why?

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.604 position:50% align:center
Come on. Do you wanna die?

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:06.022 position:50% align:center
What?

00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:08.233 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN] You're constantly
pushing yourself too hard.

00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:11.069 position:50% align:center
Heh. You believe your death
is the solution to everything,

00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:12.487 position:50% align:center
don't you?

00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:15.115 position:50% align:center
Well, you're wrong! We've been
fighting this whole time

00:10:15.198 --> 00:10:18.034 position:50% align:center
so we could find another way!

00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:20.245 position:50% align:center
We did that for you.

00:10:20.328 --> 00:10:21.705 position:50% align:center
But I'm sure you're gonna
go through with this,

00:10:21.788 --> 00:10:23.998 position:50% align:center
no matter what we say, right?

00:10:24.082 --> 00:10:25.750 position:50% align:center
I am.

00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:27.627 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN sighs]

00:10:27.711 --> 00:10:30.630 position:50% align:center
There's one thing we have to
do at any cost, you guys.

00:10:30.714 --> 00:10:32.632 position:50% align:center
We'll make sure Yuito lives.

00:10:32.716 --> 00:10:35.010 position:50% align:center
Even if he does
something reckless.

00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:39.222 position:50% align:center
[YUITO sighs]
Hanabi.

00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:43.101 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Hm...? Mm-hm.

00:10:46.855 --> 00:10:49.399 position:50% align:center
Thank you. Really.

00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:54.070 position:50% align:center
--[grunts]
--[beeping]

00:10:54.154 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50% align:center
[OSF SOLDIER A] The Suoh OSF
and the Seiran Regional Force

00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:58.450 position:50% align:center
are on the defense, sir!

00:10:58.533 --> 00:11:01.411 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] Roger. Standby for
further instructions.

00:11:01.494 --> 00:11:02.829 position:50% align:center
[OSF SOLDIER A]
Yes, sir!

00:11:06.041 --> 00:11:08.084 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Let's get one thing clear.

00:11:08.168 --> 00:11:10.462 position:50% align:center
I did lend you my
power for this,

00:11:10.545 --> 00:11:12.297 position:50% align:center
but if you try anything...

00:11:12.380 --> 00:11:14.174 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Not to worry.

00:11:14.257 --> 00:11:16.926 position:50% align:center
I promise to give
you what you want.

00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:18.553 position:50% align:center
Karen...

00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:22.182 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] Hm? Are you suspicious
of me too, little brother?

00:11:22.265 --> 00:11:25.060 position:50% align:center
No. I didn't say that.

00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:28.938 position:50% align:center
Just relax. I'll make
sure this plan works.

00:11:29.022 --> 00:11:31.316 position:50% align:center
I'll hold you to it.

00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:33.318 position:50% align:center
Well? Are we all set?

00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:35.612 position:50% align:center
We've connected to Arahabaki.

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.280 position:50% align:center
Ready to go!

00:11:37.364 --> 00:11:40.950 position:50% align:center
And this time, the two
of us can help via SAS!

00:11:41.034 --> 00:11:43.745 position:50% align:center
Alright, you guys,
here goes! Good luck!

00:11:43.828 --> 00:11:45.288 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO]
Okay!

00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:47.540 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] I understand you're
doing a lot of heavy lifting,

00:11:47.624 --> 00:11:50.543 position:50% align:center
but we really appreciate it.
We can pull this off!

00:11:50.627 --> 00:11:52.379 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
I know we'll make it work.

00:11:52.462 --> 00:11:54.964 position:50% align:center
We've been through so
much together already!

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:58.593 position:50% align:center
Well, let's go!

00:12:05.517 --> 00:12:09.020 position:50% align:center
[HARUKA]
Arahabaki. SAS link commence!

00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:23.326 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO grunt]

00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:24.994 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:12:25.078 --> 00:12:30.083 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunting]

00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:34.337 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Suoh OSF, Seiran forces,

00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:35.964 position:50% align:center
the Others have gone silent,

00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:38.383 position:50% align:center
but who knows when
they may strike again?

00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:40.176 position:50% align:center
As the defenders of New Himuka,

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:42.595 position:50% align:center
we must do what's
best for our planet,

00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:46.266 position:50% align:center
and our only option for now is
to protect the operation team!

00:12:46.349 --> 00:12:49.269 position:50% align:center
Don't let a single one of
those monsters get past you!

00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:50.562 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIERS]
Sir!

00:12:53.273 --> 00:12:55.650 position:50% align:center
First off, let's take
out the Belt!

00:12:55.734 --> 00:12:56.943 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:13:02.115 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE shouting]

00:13:13.460 --> 00:13:17.130 position:50% align:center
[shouting continues]

00:13:17.213 --> 00:13:19.883 position:50% align:center
Watching the Belt.
There's no response yet.

00:13:19.966 --> 00:13:22.719 position:50% align:center
The link to Arahabaki
hasn't quite stabilized!

00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:25.764 position:50% align:center
Yuito! Kasane!
Keep concentrating!

00:13:25.847 --> 00:13:27.807 position:50% align:center
We're trying!

00:13:27.891 --> 00:13:30.060 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] If we don't
control this power...!

00:13:32.520 --> 00:13:35.023 position:50% align:center
Damn you, start moving!

00:13:39.361 --> 00:13:42.530 position:50% align:center
[WATARU gasps] There we go!
It's shifting now!

00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:46.159 position:50% align:center
That's good, but if our minds
falter at all, we'll faint!

00:13:46.242 --> 00:13:48.286 position:50% align:center
Yeah. We'll make it!

00:13:48.370 --> 00:13:50.372 position:50% align:center
No matter what,
we can't give up!

00:13:50.455 --> 00:13:53.458 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO grunting]

00:13:58.254 --> 00:14:00.632 position:50% align:center
Just let me control
the link to Arahabaki.

00:14:00.715 --> 00:14:01.925 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:04.761 position:50% align:center
I did it for 2,000 years,
so I can handle it.

00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:06.471 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO gasp]

00:14:06.554 --> 00:14:07.722 position:50% align:center
Well?

00:14:07.806 --> 00:14:09.015 position:50% align:center
Do it!

00:14:12.018 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
--[KAREN grunts]
--[ALL gasp]

00:14:18.316 --> 00:14:20.652 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:22.529 position:50% align:center
--[YUITO] Kasane!
--[KASANE] Right!

00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:26.157 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO shout]

00:14:37.127 --> 00:14:38.628 position:50% align:center
Look at that! The Belt!

00:14:38.712 --> 00:14:39.462 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA gasps]

00:14:39.546 --> 00:14:40.463 position:50% align:center
No way!

00:14:40.547 --> 00:14:42.048 position:50% align:center
Is it working?

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:47.929 position:50% align:center
They did it! Incredible!

00:14:48.013 --> 00:14:50.348 position:50% align:center
The Gate is devouring
the Extinction Belt!

00:14:50.432 --> 00:14:51.558 position:50% align:center
Amazing.

00:14:51.641 --> 00:14:53.685 position:50% align:center
Good riddance to that thing!

00:14:56.730 --> 00:14:58.773 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER A]
I don't believe it.

00:14:58.857 --> 00:15:00.150 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER B]
But how?

00:15:03.945 --> 00:15:05.280 position:50% align:center
[KAITO]
Yuito...

00:15:09.451 --> 00:15:10.994 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
No!

00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:11.870 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
The Belt!

00:15:11.953 --> 00:15:13.413 position:50% align:center
What's happening?

00:15:22.005 --> 00:15:24.716 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI gasps]
This can't be good!

00:15:35.477 --> 00:15:38.855 position:50% align:center
Hurry, and hold the line!
Prepare to intercept!

00:15:40.732 --> 00:15:42.067 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, HANABI, LUKA]
Yuito!

00:15:52.994 --> 00:15:54.204 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:15:57.415 --> 00:15:58.625 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:14.224 --> 00:16:16.851 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Yuito, can you hear me?

00:16:16.935 --> 00:16:20.230 position:50% align:center
Hey! Wake up!

00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:23.400 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]
I'm up. Sorry.

00:16:23.483 --> 00:16:25.402 position:50% align:center
No, it's okay. You good?

00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:26.695 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:16:28.363 --> 00:16:30.240 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
It's showtime, everyone!

00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:32.242 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Let's give it our best shot!

00:16:32.325 --> 00:16:34.035 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]
Hang in there, Yuito!

00:16:34.119 --> 00:16:36.663 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI] We're going to put
all of our strength together!

00:16:39.374 --> 00:16:42.293 position:50% align:center
You said you could save the
world from destruction.

00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:44.462 position:50% align:center
Now it's time to prove it!

00:16:44.546 --> 00:16:48.550 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO shout]

00:16:48.633 --> 00:16:51.803 position:50% align:center
[KASANE, YUITO]
Here we go!

00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:04.566 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIERS shouting]

00:17:04.649 --> 00:17:06.526 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER C]
Dammit!

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:07.819 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:24.461 position:50% align:center
[YUITO, KASANE gasp]

00:17:24.544 --> 00:17:28.631 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
The Extinction Belt, it's gone!

00:17:28.715 --> 00:17:30.300 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
We can't celebrate yet.

00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:31.760 position:50% align:center
[LUKA grunts]

00:17:31.843 --> 00:17:33.845 position:50% align:center
We still need to go to the
Chronos Terminal, remember?

00:17:33.928 --> 00:17:35.930 position:50% align:center
To fix the last entanglements.

00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:37.098 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:17:37.182 --> 00:17:39.267 position:50% align:center
Oh, that won't be necessary.

00:17:39.351 --> 00:17:42.020 position:50% align:center
--[YUITO, KASANE grunt]
--[ALL gasp]

00:17:42.103 --> 00:17:44.689 position:50% align:center
--[FUBUKI] Karen!
--[LUKA] Stop it!

00:17:44.773 --> 00:17:46.399 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
I've changed my mind.

00:17:46.483 --> 00:17:48.276 position:50% align:center
I can't give up after all.

00:17:48.360 --> 00:17:49.903 position:50% align:center
Now what are you doing?

00:17:49.986 --> 00:17:51.279 position:50% align:center
No. Hold on!

00:17:51.363 --> 00:17:52.864 position:50% align:center
Think this through!

00:17:52.947 --> 00:17:55.241 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] I told you before that I
would give you what you wanted,

00:17:55.325 --> 00:17:57.202 position:50% align:center
and I'm keeping my word to you.

00:17:57.285 --> 00:17:59.996 position:50% align:center
I no longer intend
to become Yakumo.

00:18:01.623 --> 00:18:02.832 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Huh?

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:07.462 position:50% align:center
This time... will be
my last journey back.

00:18:08.755 --> 00:18:09.798 position:50% align:center
Please don't do it.

00:18:09.881 --> 00:18:11.299 position:50% align:center
Karen...

00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:20.558 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
He's gone.

00:18:34.239 --> 00:18:35.448 position:50% align:center
[ALICE]
Uh?

00:18:48.044 --> 00:18:49.254 position:50% align:center
[KAREN]
Hm.

00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:12.986 position:50% align:center
The system is detecting Red
Strings all over Suoh, but why?

00:19:13.069 --> 00:19:16.531 position:50% align:center
They're everywhere.
In Seiran and Togetsu, too.

00:19:16.614 --> 00:19:19.951 position:50% align:center
It's gotta be some kind of
widespread phenomenon!

00:19:20.035 --> 00:19:21.870 position:50% align:center
I don't understand at all.

00:19:26.875 --> 00:19:28.335 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Yuito, look!

00:19:28.418 --> 00:19:29.627 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:19:31.921 --> 00:19:33.340 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh?

00:19:37.093 --> 00:19:39.471 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
The Kunad Gate's gone.

00:19:42.265 --> 00:19:45.602 position:50% align:center
[YUITO chuckles]
That's great.

00:19:45.685 --> 00:19:48.813 position:50% align:center
Does this mean...
the world is safe?

00:19:53.068 --> 00:19:55.111 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIERS chattering]

00:19:55.195 --> 00:19:56.863 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER D]
They did it!

00:19:56.946 --> 00:19:59.908 position:50% align:center
The sky's... so blue.

00:20:05.455 --> 00:20:06.456 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN A]
Wow!

00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.458 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN B]
Isn't it wonderful?

00:20:15.715 --> 00:20:17.258 position:50% align:center
Karen...

00:20:17.342 --> 00:20:18.802 position:50% align:center
Those red lines we saw.

00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:21.721 position:50% align:center
I'm guessing they were
the Red Strings' power?

00:20:21.805 --> 00:20:25.016 position:50% align:center
When he traveled back just now,
that must have triggered

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:27.769 position:50% align:center
some drastic change
in the world.

00:20:27.852 --> 00:20:30.689 position:50% align:center
Do you mean besides the
Kunad Gate vanishing?

00:20:30.772 --> 00:20:31.856 position:50% align:center
[WATARU gasps]

00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:34.901 position:50% align:center
Oh! The sky had me distracted.

00:20:34.984 --> 00:20:36.820 position:50% align:center
Now to dig into the tech stuff!

00:20:36.903 --> 00:20:38.279 position:50% align:center
Well, sis? You game?

00:20:38.363 --> 00:20:41.116 position:50% align:center
I'm way ahead of you, bro.
Let's do it!

00:20:43.868 --> 00:20:46.121 position:50% align:center
Looks like we had some help.

00:20:46.204 --> 00:20:51.835 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]
We didn't just save the future,

00:20:51.918 --> 00:20:55.505 position:50% align:center
we destroyed the
Extinction Belt, as well.

00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:58.258 position:50% align:center
And Karen played a
major role in that.

00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:03.888 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] Yeah. We really
did forge a new future.

00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:10.520 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Karen.

00:21:10.603 --> 00:21:14.899 position:50% align:center
Can you see this same sky
from wherever you are now?

00:21:14.983 --> 00:21:17.819 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER E]
I knew we'd survive! Oh, hey!

00:21:24.492 --> 00:21:29.497 position:50% align:center
♪

00:22:55.959 --> 00:22:57.335 position:50% align:center
[WATARU]
What could this mean?

00:22:57.419 --> 00:23:00.255 position:50% align:center
All the data on Karen,
it's gone now.

00:23:00.338 --> 00:23:01.423 position:50% align:center
What?

00:23:01.506 --> 00:23:03.258 position:50% align:center
It's not in there.
I checked four times.

00:23:03.341 --> 00:23:04.634 position:50% align:center
[OSF SOLDIER D]
Major General!

00:23:06.052 --> 00:23:07.178 position:50% align:center
[OSF SOLDIER D]
From the looks of it,

00:23:07.262 --> 00:23:09.097 position:50% align:center
the operation was successful!

00:23:09.180 --> 00:23:10.807 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah.

00:23:10.890 --> 00:23:12.183 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:23:12.267 --> 00:23:14.686 position:50% align:center
[OSF SOLDIER D] Everything
turned out alright, sir!

00:23:14.769 --> 00:23:17.063 position:50% align:center
See that? We're fine!

00:23:17.147 --> 00:23:20.567 position:50% align:center
What? I-Is that you?

00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:21.735 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:23:21.818 --> 00:23:24.070 position:50% align:center
What is it?
Why are you so shocked?

00:23:24.154 --> 00:23:26.322 position:50% align:center
Well... I...

00:23:26.406 --> 00:23:30.243 position:50% align:center
[ALICE gasps]
Hanabi! Good to see you!

00:23:30.326 --> 00:23:31.578 position:50% align:center
Glad you're safe.

00:23:31.661 --> 00:23:33.830 position:50% align:center
Um, yeah, I am.

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:37.834 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Look, Alice, can I...?

00:23:37.917 --> 00:23:38.668 position:50% align:center
[ALICE]
mm?

00:23:38.752 --> 00:23:40.420 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
I'm sorry.

00:23:40.503 --> 00:23:42.839 position:50% align:center
I have something that
I need to ask you.

00:23:44.007 --> 00:23:48.219 position:50% align:center
[FUBUKI]
Listen... it's about Karen.

00:23:48.303 --> 00:23:49.471 position:50% align:center
[ALICE]
Mm?

00:23:49.554 --> 00:23:50.847 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:55.977 position:50% align:center
[ALICE]
Fubuki, who is... Karen?